      <line x1="55" y1="55" x2="225" y2="225" stroke="#C9A84C" stroke-width="0.35"/>
      <line x1="225" y1="55" x2="55" y2="225" stroke="#C9A84C" stroke-width="0.35"/>
    </svg>
    <div class="cover-top">
      <span class="logotype">Sherpa</span>
      <span class="eyebrow">Research &middot; Week Wrap Up</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-title">
      <div class="rule-bar"></div>
      <h1>Financial Advisor<br><em>Research Brief</em></h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Top 5 Stories &middot; April 24, 2026</p>
      <p class="byline">By Lawain McNeil</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Opening note -->
  <section class="opening">
    <span class="section-eyebrow">A note from Lawain</span>
    <p>Tax Day closed on Friday and the news didn&rsquo;t wait for you to breathe. FINRA scrapped the $25,000 day-trader rule. DeVoe&rsquo;s Q1 Deal Book tied the all-time record for RIA M&amp;A. Altruist&rsquo;s AI tax-planning launch sent publicly traded wealth managers down mid-single digits within days. The signal this week is clearest at the edges &mdash; regulation, capital, and technology all moving at once. Here are the five stories worth your attention.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Stories -->
  <section class="stories">
    <div class="stories-header">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Top 5 Stories This Week</span>
    </div>

    <article class="story">
      <div class="story-num">01</div>
      <div class="story-body">
        <h2><a href="https://www.investmentnews.com/regulation-legal-compliance/finras-intraday-margin-overhaul-replaces-outdated-requirements/266290" target="_blank" rel="noopener">FINRA scraps the $25,000 pattern-day-trader rule for a dynamic intraday margin framework</a></h2>
        <div class="story-meta">InvestmentNews <span class="divider">&bull;</span> Compliance</div>
        <p class="story-blurb">FINRA&rsquo;s April 20 Regulatory Notice 26-10 dismantles the 20-year-old pattern day trader framework and replaces it with intraday margin tied to actual market exposure. The rule is effective June 4, with an 18-month phase-in through October 20, 2027. If you have clients with brokerage accounts &mdash; especially active traders &mdash; every margin conversation you have for the next decade starts here.</p>
        <div class="angle">
          <span class="angle-label">Content Angle</span>
          <div class="angle-body">Write a plain-English client explainer titled &ldquo;The $25,000 day-trader rule just died &mdash; here&rsquo;s what replaces it,&rdquo; and date it in the URL so clients Googling the change find you first.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="story">
      <div class="story-num">02</div>
      <div class="story-body">
        <h2><a href="https://www.investmentnews.com/ria-news/ria-ma-off-to-a-record-start-in-2026-says-devoe-as-sellers-go-upmarket/266197" target="_blank" rel="noopener">DeVoe&rsquo;s Q1 Deal Book ties the all-time record &mdash; 93 RIA transactions in three months</a></h2>
        <div class="story-meta">InvestmentNews <span class="divider">&bull;</span> Practice Management</div>
        <p class="story-blurb">Ninety-three announced deals in Q1, up 24% year over year, tying Q3 2025 for the busiest quarter on record. Buyers are pickier &mdash; the &ldquo;vanishing middle&rdquo; of $500M&ndash;$5B firms is driving volume while the biggest deals land at platforms with scale. This isn&rsquo;t a blip. It&rsquo;s the industry rebuilding itself around two tiers, and the middle either chooses one or gets chosen for it.</p>
        <div class="angle">
          <span class="angle-label">Content Angle</span>
          <div class="angle-body">Draft a LinkedIn post for solo and mid-sized advisors titled &ldquo;Record M&amp;A is a story about you, not them&rdquo; &mdash; three bullets on what consolidation says about where independent value will actually live in 2027.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="story">
      <div class="story-num">03</div>
      <div class="story-body">
        <h2><a href="https://www.kitces.com/blog/weekend-reading-for-financial-planners-april-18-19-2026/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Altruist&rsquo;s AI tax-planning workflow launched &mdash; then publicly traded wealth managers dropped mid-single digits</a></h2>
        <div class="story-meta">Kitces (Weekend Reading) <span class="divider">&bull;</span> Advisor Tech</div>
        <p class="story-blurb">The launch itself matters less than the market&rsquo;s reaction. Within days of Altruist unveiling its AI-enabled tax-planning workflow, share prices of publicly traded wealth managers slid mid-to-high single digits. Capital is quietly pricing in a scenario where AI-native platforms compress the service moat faster than anyone modeled. Whether that&rsquo;s right or wrong, it&rsquo;s now reflected in valuations.</p>
        <div class="angle">
          <span class="angle-label">Content Angle</span>
          <div class="angle-body">Record a 60-second video for clients titled &ldquo;The technology news that moved my industry last week&rdquo; &mdash; translate the signal into plain English and let them see you metabolizing it in real time.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="story">
      <div class="story-num">04</div>
      <div class="story-body">
        <h2><a href="https://www.wealthmanagement.com/estate-planning/tax-law-update-april-2026" target="_blank" rel="noopener">The permanent $15M estate exemption is the planning conversation most advisors still haven&rsquo;t updated</a></h2>
        <div class="story-meta">WealthManagement.com <span class="divider">&bull;</span> Estate Planning</div>
        <p class="story-blurb">OBBBA made the $15M individual / $30M couple federal exemption permanent and indexed it to inflation. Most mass-affluent clients are out of the federal estate tax frame entirely. The conversation moves to state estate tax (NY, MA, OR, WA), basis step-up, and beneficiary positioning. If your playbook is still built on 2017 assumptions, your clients don&rsquo;t need a refresher &mdash; they need a rebuild.</p>
        <div class="angle">
          <span class="angle-label">Content Angle</span>
          <div class="angle-body">Send a client email titled &ldquo;If you thought your estate plan was done, please read this&rdquo; &mdash; three questions (state residency, basis strategy, beneficiaries) that replace the old federal-exemption conversation.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="story">
      <div class="story-num">05</div>
      <div class="story-body">
        <h2><a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2026/04/20/stock-market-today-live-updates.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">S&amp;P prints five straight record highs &mdash; then Iran closes Hormuz</a></h2>
        <div class="story-meta">CNBC <span class="divider">&bull;</span> Markets</div>
        <p class="story-blurb">Five consecutive record closes rolled into a 0.63% Tuesday drop after Iran re-closed the Strait of Hormuz and the US seized an Iranian cargo ship. Underneath the headlines, unemployment ticked to 4.3% on a shrinking labor force and wage growth cooled to 3.5% year over year &mdash; the same Fed-friendly combination that has kept this rally alive. The fragility is what to watch, not the peaks.</p>
        <div class="angle">
          <span class="angle-label">Content Angle</span>
          <div class="angle-body">Publish a 200-word client note titled &ldquo;Records and risks: what to watch after this week&rdquo; &mdash; three bullets (labor cooling, valuation risk, geopolitical tail risk) and a one-line close on what it doesn&rsquo;t change about their plan.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>

